s’. Putting visuality centre stage and covering political parties and non-party actors in Africa, Asia, Australia and New Zealand, Europe and the United States, contributors demonstrate the various ways in which the far right articulates natural environments and the rampant environmental crises of the twenty-first century, providing essential insights into such multifaceted politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmentalismxPolitical aspects. 0aNaturexPolitical aspects. 0aRight-wing extremists. 0aVisual communicationxPolitical aspects. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / General.2bisacsh  aclimate change.  acountryside.  aecofascism.  aecology.  aextreme right.  afascism.  alandscape.  amultimodal analysis.  apopulism.  aradical right.1 aAguilera-Carnerero, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurnett, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCagle, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampion, Kristy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarle, Zoé, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristou, Miranda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForchtner, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForchtner, Bernhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJones, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLubarda, Balša, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMišík, Matúš, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlsen, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOravcová, Veronika, econtribut